          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This goal is similar to one produced by the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/gameplaykit/gkgoal/1501236-goaltoavoidagents"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " method with a single agent and a "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "maxPredictionTime"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " parameter of zero. Affected agents will attempt to move away from the target agent, but without taking the target’s movement into account."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can also use this goal when you want an agent to move away from a target point, such as the current mouse or touch location. Create another agent that remains stationary at the target point (that is, has no velocity and no goals), and use that agent as the parameter when creating a goal with this method."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
